GTKKit is a multithreaded MVC GUI framework, which implements a UIKit-style API
on top of the GTK+ cross-platform widget toolkit. It is under active development,
and it currently in a barely usable, skeletal state.

Requirements:
 - GTK+ 3
 - ObjFW (https://webkeks.org/objfw/)

At the moment, GTKKit is only tested on OS X and FreeBSD.

Currently, GTKKit implements the following class hierarchy:

GTKResponder
  GTKView
    GTKBox
    GTKControl
      GTKButton
      GTKPupUpButton
      GTKSlider
      GTKTextField
    GTKImageView
    GTKLevelIndicator
    GTKProgressIndicator
  GTKViewController
    GTKWindowViewController
GTKImage
GTKEvent
GTKCallback
GTKApplicationDelegate
GTKLayoutConstraints
